                                  clone the scanner after use(good practice)

Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

// take input

sc.close();

    Why use sc.close()?

.Releases the Scanner resource.
.Good programming practice.
.Usually written at the end of the program.

     Is it compulsory?

❌ No, for small Java/DSA programs.
✅ Recommended in real-world applications.

Important:

After sc.close(), the Scanner cannot be used again.